In this proclamation, President Donald Trump recognizes and celebrates Jewish American Heritage Month. He acknowledges the long history and contributions of Jewish Americans to the country and the world. The proclamation also condemns anti-Semitism and highlights the need for unity and tolerance. President Trump references the recent attacks on Jewish institutions and calls for the rejection of hatred. He also mentions George Washington's letter to the Touro Synagogue, emphasizing the importance of religious liberty for all faiths in the United States. The proclamation concludes by calling upon Americans to observe Jewish American Heritage Month with appropriate programs and activities.